  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting political tolerance and non-violence among youths in Sierra Leone</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to promote inclusive and peaceful democratic participation among youth, to improve the communication and linkages between youth engagement and to promote greater interaction between civil society and National Electoral Commission on youth issues.
The project will be undertaken in the context of long-term preparations for the2022 and 2023 elections and will aim to lay the foundations for intensive engagement of both National Electoral Commission and youth serving agencies throughout the electoral period and beyond. 

This programme design is based on Caritas Sierra Leone three-pronged programming approach to addressing issues of participation and outreach. This approach focus on three elements.
- Informing and inspiring targeted groups
- Pushing for greater participation opportunities
- Encouraging institutional outreach</narrative>
  </description>
